The paper deals with the analysis of data movement requirements for parallel execution of computational directed acyclic graphs (CDAGs) on parallel systems. This topic falls under the broad area of computer architecture and parallel computing, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.AR (Computer Architecture) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with the characterization of data movement requirements for parallel algorithms on parallel computer systems. 

cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely sub-category as the paper deals with parallel execution of CDAGs on multi-node multi-core parallel systems. 

cs.PF (Performance) is another possible sub-category as the paper focuses on the balance between data movement and computational power in parallel computer systems, which is a key factor in determining performance. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as the paper analyzes the CDAGs of several numerical algorithms to develop lower bounds on data movement for their parallel execution. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper deals with the analysis of parallel systems and their inherent data movement requirements.
